      "postcode": "IP13 7SW",
      "ward": "",
      "proposal": "Listed Building Consent - Replacement of existing windows. The existing windows have late-20th century joinery detailing, which we propose to improve on by choosing a window design that reflects traditional joinery. Flush casement design is our proposal. The existing windows are double glazed and we propose that the new windows have the latest standard of double glazing. Dial Cottage is a Grade II listed thatched cottage with a late 1970?s rendered block extension. We have lived in the property for over 40 years and have received planning approval for a few changes which you will see from your records. The cottage was fitted with wooden standard casement windows some 45 years ago. The windows are starting to deteriorate. What we would like to do is to start by replacing the three on the East face of 1970's extension and then progressing over time. Our current preferred supplier is Mumford and Wood. We propose wooden flush casement windows from their Conservation Range https://mumfordwood.com/products/timber-windows/casement",
